div.div: Commented on #3352 DevFest Milano 2024 - Randstad Box | Milano, Italy - 2024/11/23

div.b:
Attendance
The attendance was heterogeneous in many ways, more than half of attendees were students and nearly half of them were women which we are really happy about. Being students our main target, we had a great number of international students.
Venue
The venue worked great and both us and the attendees were happy about it. https://www.randstadbox.it/it/vieni-in-box/
Planning vs Implementation
The schedule remained more or less the same, we run slightly late. Swag was taken entirely by the attendees. The only thing we might note is that for such events we might need bigger support, we need to work towards securing bigger funding from current and new sponsors. Positives :+1: Internation participation Gender balance in participants Great location Positive feedback from attendees Swag was greatly appreciated
Negatives
Delays in the schedule Photos

Commented on #66 feat: Add support for Notion callout blocks

This looks super cool! My only concern is that this feature is a part of ReadMe markdown, not of GitHub-Flavored Markdown. Acutally, GFM has a similar feature called alerts: https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/writing-on-github/getting-started-with-writing-and-formatting-on-github/basic-writing-and-formatting-syntax#alerts So I don't think this should be enabled by default, but it would be a cool feature to put behind some kind of flag!
